  "market_context": "Oil had a strong expansion day followed by consolidation near the previous day high around 66.72. The analyst was looking for a reversal off the previous day high as the relevant level for a retracement back into the range.",
  "key_observation": "After a sweep of the previous day high and closure back inside, the analyst anticipated a protected high formation, dropped to the 5-minute to find an entry into the fair value gap, then confirmed with a continuation entry after hourly CISD.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified oil on the hourly chart with an expansion day followed by consolidation near previous day high (66.72).",
    "Noted that a reversal off previous day high would be the relevant level for a retracement back into the range.",
    "Observed the sweep of the previous day high and closure back inside, anticipating a protected swing high (not confirmed until closure through the up-close series).",
    "Dropped to the 5-minute chart to find an early entry, identifying a continuation print and a protected high formed by the sweep into the hourly fair value gap.",
    "Took an entry giving slightly wider stop room due to oil's tendency to sweep equal highs before moving.",
    "Trade reached 2R target to the downside.",
    "Returned to the hourly to wait for confirmation — let another candle pass since price was below lows after expansion (could be retracement/consolidation/reversal).",
    "Saw price retrace back into range, respect the mean threshold, and close back inside the previous candle's range, anticipating the high to be taken.",
    "Re-dropped to 5-minute to identify a new protected high formed by sweep of short-term high and closure through up-close candles into the hourly fair value gap.",
    "Manipulated stop placement just above equal highs to achieve 2R below the lows; trade hit 2R exactly with continuation entry confirmation."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both entries (initial reversal entry and continuation entry) achieved 2R target.",
  "lessons": "Even if you miss the initial reversal entry off a protected swing, you can wait for hourly closure confirmation and look for new lower-time-frame swing points forming in the same direction for a continuation entry. Oil sometimes requires wider stops to account for equal-high sweeps.",
